description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity to join our team as an Admin Service Manager in Cardiology. You will be responsible for the professional management of the service&#39;s administrative team which supports the multi-disciplinary teams who work across the wards, outpatient areas and community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust has recently implemented a comprehensive IT system and the post holder will play an instrumental part in identifying service improvements and developing the admin structure in response to this significant change. We are looking for applicants with excellent problem solving and communication skills, the ability to remain calm under pressure as well as the confidence to work independently. You will also have significant experience of managing people and in depth knowledge of NHS administrative processes and waiting time targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
